.TH "BSON_ITER_AS_BOOL" "3" "2014-05-29" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_iter_as_bool()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
bool
bson_iter_as_bool (const bson_iter_t *iter);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B iter
A
.BR bson_iter_t
\&.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Fetches the current field as if it were a boolean.

.B bson_iter_as_bool()
currently knows how to determine a boolean value from the following types:

.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_BOOL
.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_DOUBLE
.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_INT32
.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_INT64
.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_NULL
.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_UNDEFINED
.IP \[bu] 2
BSON_TYPE_UTF8

BSON_TYPE_UTF8 will always equate to
.B true
\&.

.SH "RETURNS"

true if the field equates to non-zero.


